commentary: Henry to Misbah-ul-Haq, OUT they appeal for a caught behind and Illingworth immediately lifts the finger.. the bowler had actually given up on the appeal -- he had his hands on his head. It was only Ronchi appealing. But the bowler is pleasantly surprised. It was a bouncer again and Misbah went for a hook, but missed. This one goes over his left shoulder and looked good in the real time. Misbah reviews it immediately. The replays look like they would support Illingworth and that is what the decision is. Misbah has to go, despite him gesturing that it was off his fore-arm. He is not happy. But Henry has four now

Misbah reviews it immediately. The replays look like they would support Illingworth and that is what the decision is. Misbah has to go, despite him gesturing that it was off his fore-arm. commentary: Shahid Afridi to Ronchi, OUT oh what a stunner! Sohail Tanvir takes a blinder at long off to buoy Pakistan. Ronchi went for a big hit on this flighted delivery, but this one turned and messed up with the batsman's timing.. he ended up chipping it towards long-off. Tanvir had to run forward and dive full length - always difficult - to grab this smartly. What a strike this is!

commentary: Haris Sohail to Vettori, 4 leg byes goes for the reverse-sweep but this one slides off the glove/pad down to the boundary.. Over? No. Afridi wants a review. Was he hit in front of the off there? Can't say really. If he has missed, and it's out, it's another wicket for Haris Sohail, so important for him. What fun right at the end! It's missing off... so it's Game Over officially. Signalled four leg byes
